g.name: cAMP up due to ADORA2A ->Coronary artery vasodilatation ->Decreased dopaminergic activity in CNS ->Inhibition of central neuron excitation.

cAMP down due to ADORA3 ->Cardiac muscle relaxation ->Smooth muscle contraction ->Cardioprotective in cardiac ischemia ->Inhibition of neutrophil degranulation
